CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 21, 1956, p. 1, reads: "No City Help - Apple St. residents on Monday said that the city turned a deaf ear to their pleas for "Go Slow" signs or other measures to insure safety in this area, which has been made into a one-way street by the sliding of loose earth from the Belmar Gardens' hillside above. - "Teenie" Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Landslide cordoned off by wooden fence, with car on right with 1956 Pennsylvania license plate L138R, possibly Alma Speed Fox on left, and William "Woogie" Harris' house at 7101 Apple Street in background, Homewood
